## Interview Prep

#JavaScript: language that runs on the BROWSER

#Node.js: javascript that runs on a computer

#Library: import code from other people

#getElement ById/ClassName/Tag: 1 element or array of elements

#class: many items

#id: one item

#<p class='myClass1' myClass2 myClass3 		CSS: .yClass1
#<p id="myid"								CSS: #Myid



#Style tag in CSS:

	Inline: 	<p style="background-color:red;"
	Internal: 	<style> in HEAD normally
	External: 	style.css 	link with <link href="style.css" rel="stylesheet">
#Script tag in CSS:
	
	INLINE: 	<button onclick="alert('hi')">
	Internal:	<script></script>
	EXTERNAL: 	index.js






